quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  42,52,"As such We have revealed to you (Prophet Muhammad) a spirit (the revelation of the Koran) from Our Ordinance. You did not know what the Book was, nor belief, but We made it a light whereby We guide those of Our worshipers whom We will. And you (Prophet Muhammad), you, surely guide to a Straight Path."
  42,53,"The Path of Allah, to whom belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is in the earth. Surely, to Allah all things return."
  43,1,"HaMeem."
  43,2,"By the Clear Book"
  43,3,"We have made it an Arabic Koran in order that you understand."
  43,4,"It is in the Origin of the Book with Us, sublime and wise."
  43,5,"Shall We turn away the Remembrance from you because you are a sinful nation?"
  43,6,"How many a Prophet did We send to the ancients,"
  43,7,"no Prophet came to them except that they mocked him,"
  43,8,"so We destroyed those who were mightier in courage than they. And the example of the ancients has passed away."
  43,9,"Yet, if you ask them who created the heavens and the earth, they will answer: 'The Almighty, the Knower created them'"
  43,10,"(It is) He who made the earth to be a cradle for you and made in it ways for you, in order that you are guided."